New Records: Ronald Acuña Jr. became the first person in MLB history to hit 30 homers and steal 60 bases in a season.
Key Match Events: The Atlanta Braves defeated the Philadelphia Phillies 4-1 to clinch the NL East title.
Matt Olson leads the majors with 51 homers and 128 RBI.
Spencer Strider has 259 strikeouts, the most in the majors.
Post-Match Reflections: The Braves clinched the division on Wednesday night, becoming the first team to punch their ticket to the 2023 MLB Postseason.
The Braves have been kings of their division since 2018, but this year's squad may be the best they've had in their recent run.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Braves' lead over the Phillies is the largest between top-two seeds in any division.
Atlanta's offense leads the majors in average, on-base percentage, slugging percentage, and runs.
The Braves' relievers owned a combined 3.56 ERA, the third-lowest mark among MLB bullpens.
